Note:
Master Test Runner for Advanced Macros Library

Coordinates comprehensive testing of all macro modules including:
- Core macro system functionality and registry management
- Macro expansion engine and pipeline operations
- Advanced code generation capabilities 
- Domain-specific language creation tools
- Variable hygiene and scoping system
- Custom syntax extension framework
- Enterprise-grade production macro processing
- Cross-module integration testing
- Performance benchmarking across all modules
- Production readiness validation
:End Note

Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/macros/system" as MacroSystem
Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/macros/expansion" as MacroExpansion
Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/macros/code_generation" as CodeGeneration
Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/macros/dsl_support" as DSLSupport
Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/macros/hygiene" as MacroHygiene
Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/macros/syntax_extensions" as SyntaxExtensions
Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/macros/production_system" as ProductionSystem
Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/utilities/common" as Common

Note: Import individual module test suites
Import "./test_system" as SystemTests
Import "./test_expansion" as ExpansionTests
Import "./test_code_generation" as CodeGenerationTests
Import "./test_dsl_support" as DSLSupportTests
Import "./test_hygiene" as HygieneTests
Import "./test_syntax_extensions" as SyntaxExtensionTests
Import "./test_production_system" as ProductionSystemTests

Note: Test Configuration Constants
Let INTEGRATION_TEST_TIMEOUT be 60000.0
Let PERFORMANCE_BENCHMARK_DURATION be 15000.0
Let STRESS_TEST_ITERATIONS be 200
Let PRODUCTION_READINESS_THRESHOLD be 99.5

Note: Test Result Tracking
Let total_tests be 0
Let total_passed be 0
Let total_failed be 0
Let module_results be Dictionary[String, Dictionary[String, Any]] containing

Process called "run_module_tests" that takes module_name as String and test_runner as Function returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Display message "\n" plus "=" repeated 60
    Display message "Running " plus module_name plus " Module Tests"
    Display message "=" repeated 60
    
    Let start_time be Common.get_current_timestamp()
    
    Try:
        Let module_result be test_runner()
        Let end_time be Common.get_current_timestamp()
        
        Let execution_time be end_time minus start_time
        
        Note: Extract results from the module test results
        Let tests_run be module_result["tests_run"]
        Let tests_passed be module_result["tests_passed"] 
        Let tests_failed be module_result["tests_failed"]
        Let module_success be module_result.get("success", (tests_failed is equal to 0))
        
        If module_success:
            Display message "✅ " plus module_name plus " tests PASSED: " plus tests_passed plus "/" plus tests_run
        Otherwise:
            Display message "❌ " plus module_name plus " tests FAILED: " plus tests_failed plus " failures out of " plus tests_run
            If "error" in module_result:
                Display message "  Error: " plus module_result["error"]
        
        Return Dictionary[String, Any] containing:
            "success" as module_success
            "execution_time_ms" as execution_time
            "tests_run" as tests_run
            "tests_passed" as tests_passed
            "tests_failed" as tests_failed
            "details" as module_result
            
    Catch error:
        Let end_time be Common.get_current_timestamp()
        Let execution_time be end_time minus start_time
        
        Display message "💥 " plus module_name plus " module tests CRASHED: " plus error.message
        
        Return Dictionary[String, Any] containing:
            "success" as false
            "execution_time_ms" as execution_time
            "tests_run" as 0
            "tests_passed" as 0
            "tests_failed" as 1
            "error" as error.message

Note: Core Module Tests

Process called "run_system_tests" returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Execute comprehensive system tests and capture real results
    Try:
        SystemTests.run_all_system_tests()
        Return Dictionary[String, Any] containing:
            "tests_run" as SystemTests.test_count
            "tests_passed" as SystemTests.passed_count
            "tests_failed" as SystemTests.failed_count
            "module" as "system"
            "success" as (SystemTests.failed_count is equal to 0)
    Catch error:
        Return Dictionary[String, Any] containing:
            "tests_run" as 0
            "tests_passed" as 0
            "tests_failed" as 1
            "module" as "system"
            "success" as false
            "error" as error.message

